#NextGenATP Mensik & Fonseca: Jakub Mensik and Joao Fonseca, two of the brightest young prospects on the ATP Tour, both return to action after opening-round losses in Shanghai and Brussels, respectively. Fonseca faces defending champion Giovanni Mpetshi Perricard in his Basel debut.

Cousins Vacherot, Rinderknech Return: After their fairytale run in Shanghai, where World No. 204 Vacherot defeated Arthur Rinderknech in the final to become the lowest-ranked ATP Masters 1000 champion, the duo returns to court. Vacherot has since rocketed inside the Top 40.

Bolelli & Vavassori's Turin Quest: Simone Bolelli and Andrea Vavassori are the second seeds in the double's draw. The Italians are seventh in the PIF ATP Live Doubles Teams Rankings and aiming to return to the Nitto ATP Finals. They will face competition from top seeds Marcel Granollers and Horacio Zeballos. 



